The paper focuses on identifying appropriate indicators for evaluating individual researchers, which involves analyzing publication and citation data. This aligns with several sub-categories in computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), cybersecurity (cs.CY), cryptography (cs.CR), and social and information networks (cs.SI). However, given the emphasis on publication and citation data, cs.DL and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories.
